cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.NE 

The paper presents a neural network-based approach to discover and predict the dynamics of a multi-agent system. This involves formulating a coupled non-linear network with a generic ODE-based state evolution and developing a time-discretized model. The paper also discusses tuning the network to learn agent-specific parameters of the dynamics to ensure accurate prediction even when physical or relational attributes of agents, or number of agents change. Given these aspects, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper presents a neural network-based approach to discover and predict the dynamics of a multi-agent system, which falls under the scope of machine learning. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with modeling and predicting the dynamics of a complex system, which is a key aspect of systems and control. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper involves developing an AI-based approach to discover and predict the dynamics of a multi-agent system. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper deals with modeling and predicting the dynamics of a multi-agent system, which falls under the scope of multiagent systems. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper involves developing a neural network-based approach to discover and predict the dynamics of a multi-agent system, which falls under the scope of neural and evolutionary computing.
